        "\n",
        "# Git Usage\n",
        "\n",
        "In this section, we'll explore how to use Git for version control in your projects. You'll learn how to create repositories, manage changes with commits, view history, work with branches, and resolve conflicts. We'll also cover advanced features like tagging and undoing changes.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Creating a Repository\n",
        "\n",
        "A **repository** is a directory where Git tracks changes to your files. To create a new repository, navigate to your desired directory and initialize Git:"
      ],
      "id": "aa06bc77"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "# Initialize a new Git repository\n",
        "!git init"
      ],
      "id": "176bccd4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Once initialized, a hidden `.git` folder is created. This folder contains all the metadata for your repository. It's important not to modify anything inside this folder unless you are well-versed in Git.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Creating the History: Commits\n",
        "\n",
        "**Commits** are snapshots of your repository at specific points in time. Each commit records the state of your files and allows you to revert to that state in the future.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Staging Files for Commit\n",
        "\n",
        "Before committing changes, you need to stage them. Staging allows you to choose which files to include in a commit. Let's create a file and check the repository status:"
      ],
      "id": "8a2939fe"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "# Create a new file and add content\n",
        "!echo 'My first commit!' > README.txt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Check the repository status\n",
        "!git status"
      ],
      "id": "22fb18d4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Git will show the following output:"
      ],
      "id": "aeaad04c"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| \n",
        "On branch master\n",
        "Initial commit\n",
        "Untracked files:\n",
        "  (use \"git add <file>...\" to include in what will be committed)\n",
        "  README.txt\n",
        "nothing added to commit but untracked files present (use \"git add\" to track)"
      ],
      "id": "d5fd6e9c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "This means that `README.txt` is untracked. To stage it for commit, use the `git add` command:"
      ],
      "id": "b85b28ad"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "# Stage the file for commit\n",
        "!git add README.txt\n",
        "\n",
        "# Check the repository status again\n",
        "!git status"
      ],
      "id": "48830957",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Now the file is staged and ready to be committed.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Making a Commit\n",
        "\n",
        "To save changes, create a commit with a descriptive message:"
      ],
      "id": "21c576dc"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "#| \n",
        "# Commit the staged file\n",
        "!git commit -m \"Initial commit with README.txt\""
      ],
      "id": "dd26c9fe",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "This creates a new snapshot in the repository history. Each commit is uniquely identified by a **SHA1 hash**.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Adding All Changes\n",
        "To stage all changes in the current directory, use:"
      ],
      "id": "60472379"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "# Add all changes\n",
        "!git add ."
      ],
      "id": "d8e098a4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "this will add all the changes in the current directory to the staging area. if you altered a file after it was added to the staging area, git graph will require you to create \"**new**\" commit and it will appear with different Hash.\n",
        "```{mermaid}\n",
        "%%{\n",
        "  init: {\n",
        "    'theme': 'base',\n",
        "    'themeVariables': {\n",
        "      'primaryColor': '#89CFF0',\n",
        "      'primaryTextColor': '#000000',\n",
        "      'primaryBorderColor': '#003366',\n",
        "      'lineColor': '#003366',\n",
        "      'secondaryColor': '#ffffff',\n",
        "      'secondaryTextColor': '#006100'\n",
        "    }\n",
        "  }\n",
        "}%%\n",
        "    gitGraph\n",
        "       commit id: \"Head\"\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Viewing the History\n",
        "\n",
        "To view the commit history of your repository, use the `git log` command:\n"
      ],
      "id": "7a8641c7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# View the commit history\n",
        "!git log"
      ],
      "id": "73a8a609",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "For a more visual representation, you can use the following command to display a graph of commits:\n"
      ],
      "id": "4b5b7798"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display a commit graph\n",
        "!git log --all --graph --decorate --oneline"
      ],
      "id": "63a0ef7f",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Independent Development Lines: Branches\n",
        "\n",
        "Git allows you to work on **branches**, which are independent paths of development. By default, your repository starts on the `master` branch. You can create and switch to a new branch as follows:\n"
      ],
      "id": "c3c9460d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create and switch to a new branch\n",
        "!git branch develop\n",
        "!git checkout develop"
      ],
      "id": "f612cee1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Now, all commits will be added to the `develop` instead of `master`.\n",
        "\n",
        "```{mermaid}\n",
        "%%{\n",
        "  init: {\n",
        "    'theme': 'base',\n",
        "    'themeVariables': {\n",
        "      'primaryColor': '#89CFF0',\n",
        "      'primaryTextColor': '#000000',\n",
        "      'primaryBorderColor': '#003366',\n",
        "      'lineColor': '#003366',\n",
        "      'secondaryColor': '#ffffff',\n",
        "      'secondaryTextColor': '#006100'\n",
        "    }\n",
        "  }\n",
        "}%%\n",
        "    gitGraph\n",
        "       commit id: \"Head\"\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       branch develop\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       checkout main\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "### Example: Isolating Changes in a Branch\n",
        "\n",
        "Let's make changes in `develop`:"
      ],
      "id": "99b33ae6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# Modify the file and commit changes\n",
        "!echo 'Changes in develop' >> README.txt\n",
        "!git add README.txt\n",
        "!git commit -m \"Changes in develop\""
      ],
      "id": "5a864659",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Switching back to `master` will show the previous state of the repository:\n"
      ],
      "id": "5d5257b1"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# Switch back to master\n",
        "!git checkout master"
      ],
      "id": "c0ad4be1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Combining Histories: Merging Branches\n",
        "\n",
        "To merge changes from one branch into another, switch to the destination branch and use the `git merge` command:"
      ],
      "id": "a6ee9b65"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# Merge develop into master\n",
        "!git checkout master\n",
        "!git merge develop"
      ],
      "id": "0cbaa85d",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Git may perform a **fast-forward merge**, where the branch history is linear. To preserve the history as a tree, use:"
      ],
      "id": "686d5c60"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# Merge with no fast-forward\n",
        "!git merge --no-ff develop"
      ],
      "id": "80b64c95",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "```{mermaid}\n",
        "%%{\n",
        "  init: {\n",
        "    'theme': 'base',\n",
        "    'themeVariables': {\n",
        "      'primaryColor': '#89CFF0',\n",
        "      'primaryTextColor': '#000000',\n",
        "      'primaryBorderColor': '#003366',\n",
        "      'lineColor': '#003366',\n",
        "      'secondaryColor': '#ffffff',\n",
        "      'secondaryTextColor': '#006100'\n",
        "    }\n",
        "  }\n",
        "}%%\n",
        "    gitGraph\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       branch develop\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       checkout main\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       merge develop\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "       commit\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Resolving Merge Conflicts\n",
        "\n",
        "Conflicts occur when changes in two branches overlap. Let's simulate a conflict:\n"
      ],
      "id": "37164455"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# In develop\n",
        "!git checkout develop\n",
        "!echo 'Conflict in develop' >> file.txt\n",
        "!git add file.txt\n",
        "!git commit -m \"Conflict in develop\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# In master\n",
        "!git checkout master\n",
        "!echo 'Conflict in master' >> file.txt\n",
        "!git add file.txt\n",
        "!git commit -m \"Conflict in master\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Try merging\n",
        "!git merge develop"
      ],
      "id": "72c99188",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Git will display a conflict message:"
      ],
      "id": "ff79372f"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "CONFLICT (content): Merge conflict in file.txt\n",
        "Automatic merge failed; fix conflicts and then commit the result."
      ],
      "id": "01b51336",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Open the conflicted file and resolve the differences by choosing one version or combining changes. Once resolved, add the file and complete the merge:\n"
      ],
      "id": "011c9e02"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add the resolved file and commit\n",
        "!git add file.txt\n",
        "!git commit"
      ],
      "id": "a6a39ac3",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Tagging Important Points\n",
        "\n",
        "Tags mark specific milestones in your repository, such as releases. To create a tag:\n"
      ],
      "id": "bb0a5da0"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create an annotated tag\n",
        "!git tag -a v1.0 -m \"Version 1.0 release\""
      ],
      "id": "632ac9ad",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "List all tags with:\n"
      ],
      "id": "94c88dcf"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "# List tags\n",
        "!git tag"
      ],
      "id": "ee5c0c25",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Undoing Changes\n",
        "\n",
        "Git allows you to undo changes at various levels:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Modify the Last Commit**:\n"
      ],
      "id": "e0afd6e9"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "   # Amend the last commit\n",
        "   !git commit --amend -m \"Updated commit message\""
      ],
      "id": "591759d7",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "2. **Discard Changes**:\n"
      ],
      "id": "f0bb1370"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "   # Discard uncommitted changes\n",
        "   !git checkout -- file.txt"
      ],
      "id": "9b46c545",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "3. **Delete Commits**:\n"
      ],
      "id": "826c4ac7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "#| echo: true\n",
        "\n",
        "   # Remove the last commit\n",
        "   !git reset --hard HEAD~1"
      ],
